id: pm-k0nl2w
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-2E: directory-shaped settings.json crashes CLI bootstrap"
description: "Harden settings bootstrap so a settings.json path that exists but is not a readable regular file yields deterministic settings diagnostics instead of propagating EISDIR before health, validation, or storage-integrity commands can run."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: "area:config","area:storage",observability,resilience,sentry
created_at: "2026-07-21T12:25:47.265Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T15:21:22.684Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T13:31:20.685Z"
author: codex-root
acceptance_criteria: "Directory-shaped or otherwise unreadable settings.json never crashes readSettingsWithMetadata; callers receive a deterministic warning and fallback settings; normal, missing, invalid-JSON, and invalid-schema behavior remains stable; CLI acceptance, full exact coverage, release gates, and the live Sentry gate pass."
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: high
confidence: high
severity: high
environment: production
repro_steps: "Create .agents/pm/settings.json as a directory and run any pm command that bootstraps settings, such as pm health --check-only."
resolution: "Separated filesystem diagnostics, bypassed cache for transient read failures, and made semantic background work durable through delayed replacement dispatch plus settings-race re-enqueue."
expected_result: CLI bootstrap remains available and surfaces a machine-readable settings warning that directs the operator to repair the unreadable settings path.
actual_result: "Directory-shaped settings.json yields uncached settings_read_fs_error diagnostics and remediation; permission-only recovery is visible on the next read; semantic queue workers retain a bounded delayed runner and re-enqueue IDs across settings races; 6,061 tests pass at exact 100/100/100/100 coverage."
affected_version: 2026.7.21
fixed_version: next
component: core/store/settings
regression: true
